			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=833')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=38300&amp;TOPIC_ID=4840&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=What+Tactics+make+a+CoS+so+valuable%3F%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         What makes a Circlet of Shadow so invaluable?  Instant cast invisibility.  Because it's insta-cast you don't have to be standing still nor is there a delay that's normally associated with casting invis. </P><P>Tactics explained that have been mentioned that you can't do w/o one.</P><P>FD-Getup.  FD in front of a bunch of MOB's or a stationary MOB (that FD makes you drop agro from).  Normally you can't do anything except wait for FD to refresh run some more and FD again.  With a Circlet, if your clicks/finger/macro is fast enough you can get up and invis right in front of the MOB with no agro.</P><P>Invis Pulling - Normally you agro a MOB you run by his buddies and you then have the beginnings of a great agro train.  With a circlet, you agro the MOB and start running to where ever you want.  Because it's insta-click invis, you click invis on the run and do NOT agro anything that doesn't see thru invis.  If your invis drops for some reason, click it again.</P><P>Exploring - There is no delay in a cast time associated with the Circlet, so you can stand right in front of Ready To Attack MOB_01 and click your circlet all day.  They won't agro.</P><P>Poofing Pet - Handy, but probably not as big a deal anymore.  Slim get's a mind of his own.  Click...instant Slim Perm-Time-Out.</P><P>It doesn't allow you to do anything you can't do invis, but it does allow you to do many things much better.  These are only some of the uses, it's a must have for any Necro or SK.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95266" target="_blank">Kuotat Smith</a><BR><s>Warlock</s> Witch<BR>Mithaniel Marr<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
